      <memberdef kind="variable" id="structbt__l2cap__le__chan_1a716ea69cb7261076023d0cf6384b3ebb" prot="public" static="no" mutable="no">
        <type>struct <ref refid="structk__fifo" kindref="compound">k_fifo</ref></type>
        <definition>struct k_fifo bt_l2cap_le_chan::tx_queue</definition>
        <argsstring></argsstring>
        <name>tx_queue</name>
        <qualifiedname>bt_l2cap_le_chan::tx_queue</qualifiedname>
        <briefdescription>
<para>Channel Transmission queue. </para>
        </briefdescription>
        <detaileddescription>
<para>Internal</para>
<para>SDUs/PDUs given to <ref refid="group__bt__l2cap_1ga97b7909749667f910f83e6fcb54495c3" kindref="member">bt_l2cap_chan_send</ref> and <computeroutput>bt_l2cap_send_pdu</computeroutput> are stored here until they are sent to the Controller.</para>
<para>The SDU header is prepended to SDUs before they are stored here. The head of this list (the next data to be sent) may be just the remaining part of an already partially transmitted SDU/PDU due to L2CAP segmentation and fragmentation.</para>
<para>This is the outbox for a single channel. Channels may be serviced in any order. The transmission order does not follow the sequence of <ref refid="group__bt__l2cap_1ga97b7909749667f910f83e6fcb54495c3" kindref="member">bt_l2cap_chan_send</ref> calls across channels.</para>
<para>There may be more data here than the channel currently has credits for. The transmission will wait until credits are available.</para>
<para>Callbacks given to <ref refid="group__bt__l2cap_1ga97b7909749667f910f83e6fcb54495c3" kindref="member">bt_l2cap_chan_send</ref> are stored in the user_data of the buffer. These callbacks must be invoked when the Controller gives a Number of Buffers Complete Event for the last L2CAP PDU of the buffer or when the channel is disconnected. </para>
        </detaileddescription>
        <inbodydescription>
        </inbodydescription>
        <location file="zephyr/bluetooth/l2cap.h" line="294" column="13" bodyfile="zephyr/bluetooth/l2cap.h" bodystart="294" bodyend="-1"/>
